# {{ py_project_root }}/{{ ai_source_root }}/agents/ — the AI services

Each subpackage is one deployable agent service: a FastAPI app factory with
`/health` and versioned `/api/v1/*` routes, its own pydantic `settings.py`
reading `.env`, and Makefile lifecycle targets (`make <name>-up` /
`<name>-down` / `<name>-chat`, underscores as dashes).

{% if primary_chat_agent in ["lg_agent", "both"] -%}
- `{{ lg_agent_dir }}/` — the user-facing chat agent (LangGraph): graph +
  nodes (`retrieve` → `generate` → `guardrail`), checkpointer-backed
  conversation state, BM25 retrieval over the `core/pipelines/corpus/` index, MCP tool wiring
  via `clients/mcp.py`.
{% endif -%}
{% if primary_chat_agent in ["adk_agent", "both"] -%}
- `{{ adk_agent_dir }}/` — {% if primary_chat_agent == "both" %}the same assistant role built on Google ADK (comparison implementation){% else %}the user-facing chat agent (Google ADK){% endif %}:
  router + sub-agents (`direct_agent`, `rag_agent`), prompt files under
  `prompts/`, FastAPI gateway under `gateway/`.
{% endif -%}
{% if include_rag_agent -%}
- `rag_agent/` — the retrieval backend (LangGraph + embedding vector store).
  Serves `POST /api/v1/retrieval` — the contract the MCP `search_articles`
  tool calls via `RAG_AGENT_URL`. `make rag-up` / `make rag-chat`;
  `make rag-corpus-ingest` builds its vector store.
{% endif -%}
